Creates a Submit and start the Review process.
 @param _ipfsHash Hash of the submitter Paper.*

TODO: Add proper parameters
 TODO: Add process of finding reviewers*

params._requests: List of the requests asked by the reviewer. The front will ask the reviewer the status of its review, and right after it will ask if he wants to add ChangeRequests. The reviewer will create _requests array the front which will call 'createChangeRequest'*

params._status: What the reviewers think should happen next to the submit.*

params._comment: What the reviewers think is not okay or wants changed
params._line: The line concerned by the comment (-1 if it's for the whole paper) Due to the length of a call to a contract, I think it would be best if the front can create the changeRequests by itself.*
params._page: The page concerned by the comment (-1 if it's for the whole paper)

params._status: what the reviewers think should happen next (accept, reject, change).*

newSubmit(string).notice: Add a submit to "userToSubmits" if it doesn't exists.

submitPaper(string).notice: Creates a Submit and start the Review process.
